Results.ReviewText: Having decided to stop having sugar with my coffee I tried various brands and various types. This was my favourite as it has a great coffee taste but not sharp and it was actually better without anything added. I now don't take sugar in any coffee whether black or white but this continues to be one of my favourite coffees
Results.Title: A coffee treat

Results.ReviewText: I am not the greatest coffee fan, as normally people make it way too strong for me to drink.  However, I have never known anyone make a bad cup of Cap Colombie.  I absolutely adore the aroma and taste of this coffee, and its always top of my list when buying coffee :)
Results.Title: Perfect Strength and Flavour Combination

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for getting in touch! We have recently updated the packaging of Cap Colombie however we have not made any changes to the recipe. We'll certainly make a note of your comments though & let the rest of the team know your thoughts.

Results.ReviewText: I have been buying this coffee since Cafe Parisien disappeared from the shelves.  It has been a fine compromise until recently when the taste has become very flat and stale. I will be seeking another alternative now.
Results.Title: Tastes Stale

ClientResponses.Response: Hi Mikey, although we've given the jar a bit of a refresh, we've not made any changes to the recipe of Cap Colombie. If you're still having problems please get in touch here: https://www.nestle.co.uk/getintouch/contactus

Results.ReviewText: The jar has recently changed and with it too the taste - it now leaves and aftertaste and tastes like a cheaper Aldi type coffee which is not good!  Can someone from Necafe please sort this as it was the only coffee I could drink!

Results.ReviewText: I buy this all the time the taste is as good as having coffee made from my bean to cup machine. It is simply the closest instant coffee I have ever had to my machine and I cant stress enough how good the taste actually is
Results.Title: the taste is the best i have ever had

ClientResponses.Response: Hello, it's disappointing to hear you don't enjoy the changes we've made to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. Due to the addition of micro ground coffee during the recent change there may be a residue at the bottom of your cup. Micro ground coffee is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! We haven't made any recent changes to our other blends.
